-- UK's Osborne appoints U.S. academic Forbes to Bank of England MPC
-- By David Milliken and William James
-- Thu May 15, 2014 08:01AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 15 (Reuters) - Britain's finance minister George Osborne said on Thursday he had appointed U.S. academic Kristin Forbes to the Bank of England's rate-setting Monetary Policy Committee.

"Dr Kristin Forbes is an economist of outstanding ability with real practical experience of policy making," Osborne said in a statement from his office.